[2026-03-13T19:58:53Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013Y5EJhPZgAJrRFK4ZZsW2U","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary document:\n\n## Summary: Cloche Logs System Architecture\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the cloche codebase. Below is a comprehensive analysis of how the logs system works, organized by component.\n\n### 1. CLI Command Implementation\n\n**File: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 347-432)**\n\nThe `cloche logs` command:\n- Takes a run ID and optional filters: `--step <name>`, `--type <full|script|llm>`, `--follow/-f`\n- Uses gRPC metadata header `x-cloche-follow` to signal follow mode (tail -f behavior)\n- Calls `client.StreamLogs()` with a `StreamLogsRequest` containing run ID, step name filter, and log type filter\n- Processes `LogEntry` messages from the stream and formats them for display\n- Supports different entry types: `step_started`, `step_completed`, `run_completed`, `full_log`, and filtered log types\n\n**Key code snippet:**\n```go\n// Follow mode via gRPC metadata\nif follow {\n    md := metadata.Pairs(\"x-cloche-follow\", \"true\")\n    ctx = metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)\n}\nstream, err := client.StreamLogs(ctx, &pb.StreamLogsRequest{...})\n```\n\n### 2. gRPC Service Definition\n\n**File: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 10, 62-76)**\n\nTwo key message types:\n- `StreamLogsRequest`: Contains `run_id`, `step_name`, `log_type`, and `follow` flag\n- `LogEntry`: Contains `type`, `step_name`, `result`, `message`, `timestamp`\n\nThe `StreamLogs` RPC is a server-streaming RPC that returns `stream LogEntry`.\n\n### 3. Daemon-Side Handler\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 487-726)**\n\nThe `StreamLogs` method (lines 487-596) implements the core logic:\n\n**Path 1: Full Log File (lines 516-535)**\n- Checks if `full.log` exists in `.cloche/<run-id>/output/full.log`\n- If found, sends the entire contents as a single `full_log` type entry\n- For completed runs, sends a `run_completed` entry\n\n**Path 2: Active Run with Follow Mode (lines 507-509)**\n- Uses the log broadcaster to subscribe to live updates\n- Calls `streamFollowLogs()` which combines snapshot + live streaming\n\n**Path 3: Filtered Logs (lines 500-501)**\n- Routes to `streamFilteredLogs()` for step or log_type filtering\n\n**Path 4: Fallback Capture-Based Streaming (lines 537-596)**\n- Uses the CaptureStore to get per-step execution records\n- Reads individual step output files (`.log` or `.out`)\n- Constructs LogEntry messages for each step\n\n### 4. Domain Types\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`**\n\nCore types:\n- `Run`: Contains ID, workflow name, state, active steps, step executions, timestamps, project dir, error message, container ID, etc.\n- `StepExecution`: Tracks step name, result, start/completion times, logs, git reference\n- `RunState`: Enum with values `pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n\nStep executions are recorded when:\n- Step starts: `RecordStepStart(stepName)` (line 72)\n- Step completes: `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` (line 80)\n\n### 5. Port Interfaces\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`**\n\nThree key interfaces:\n\n**RunStore Interface (lines 10-20):**\n- Methods: `CreateRun`, `GetRun`, `UpdateRun`, `DeleteRun`, `ListRuns`, `ListRunsByProject`, `ListRunsFiltered`, `ListProjects`, `ListChildRuns`\n\n**CaptureStore Interface (lines 22-25):**\n- Methods: `SaveCapture(runID, StepExecution)`, `GetCaptures(runID)`\n- Stores per-step execution records (start/completion times, result)\n\n**LogStore Interface (lines 37-42):**\n- Methods: `SaveLogFile`, `GetLogFiles`, `GetLogFilesByStep`, `GetLogFileByType`\n- Uses `LogFileEntry` type with fields: ID, RunID, StepName, FileType (full/script/llm), FilePath, FileSize, CreatedAt\n\n### 6. SQLite Adapter Implementation\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`**\n\nDatabase schema:\n- `runs`: Stores run metadata (id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, timestamps, etc.)\n- `step_executions`: Stores per-step execution records with full step data\n- `log_files`: Indexes extracted log files with metadata (lines 91-103)\n- Additional tables: `merge_queue`, `evolution_log`\n\nKey methods:\n- `CreateRun()` (line 134): Creates a new run record\n- `SaveCapture()` (line 309): Inserts a step execution record\n- `SaveLogFile()` (line 343): Indexes a log file entry\n- `GetLogFilesByStep()`, `GetLogFileByType()` (lines 364-383): Queries indexed log files\n\n### 7. Output Capture in Container Agent\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`**\n\nThe agent runner (lines 37-121):\n1. Creates a unified log writer via `logstream.New()` (line 69)\n2. Executes the workflow engine\n3. On each step completion, calls `logStepOutput()` to copy per-step logs to the unified log\n4. Writes to `.cloche/output/full.log` via the `logstream.Writer`\n\nFor agent prompt steps specifically (lines 171-180):\n- Copies `<step>.log` to `llm-<step>.log` for filtering\n\n### 8. Unified Log Writer\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go`**\n\nThe `Writer` type (lines 21-67):\n- Appends to `.cloche/output/full.log` with thread-safe locking\n- Each entry is formatted as: `[timestamp] [type] message`\n- Type can be: `status`, `script`, or `llm`\n- Multi-line messages are split into separate entries\n\n```go\ntype Writer struct {\n    mu   sync.Mutex\n    file *os.File\n    Now  func() time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### 9. Output Capture in Host Executor\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`**\n\nThe host executor (lines 1-278):\n- Script steps (lines 92-156): Execute shell commands, write output to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step>.out` or `.log`\n- Workflow steps (lines 158-221): Dispatch container runs and poll for completion\n- Agent steps (lines 223-278): Execute agent commands via the prompt adapter\n\nStep output files are stored in the executor's `OutputDir` which is typically `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`.\n\n### 10. Log Broadcast for Live Streaming\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`**\n\nThe `Broadcaster` type implements pub/sub for live log streaming:\n- `Subscribe(runID)`: Returns a channel for receiving log lines\n- `Publish(runID, LogLine)`: Broadcasts to all subscribers (non-blocking, drops on full buffer)\n- `Finish(runID)`: Closes all subscriber channels when run completes\n\nUsed in gRPC server (line 80 in grpc/server.go) to stream live output during active runs.\n\n### 11. Protocol Messages\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` (lines 1-88)**\n\nThe `StatusWriter` type writes JSON-formatted status messages to a stream:\n- `StepStarted(stepName)`\n- `StepCompleted(stepName, result)`\n- `RunCompleted(result)`\n- `RunTitle(title)`\n- `Log(stepName, message)` — for live streaming\n- `Error(stepName, message)`\n\nThese messages are parsed by the daemon's `trackRun()` method (lines 192-278 in grpc/server.go) to update run state and broadcast logs.\n\n### 12. Log File Indexing\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 1198-1251)**\n\nThe `indexLogFiles()` method scans the output directory after container completion:\n- Identifies log files by naming convention:\n  - `full.log` → type: \"full\"\n  - `llm-<step>.log` → type: \"llm\", step: \\<step\\>\n  - `<step>.log` → type: \"script\", step: \\<step\\>\n  - `container.log` → internal, not indexed\n- Creates `LogFileEntry` records in the log store\n\n### 13. Log Extraction from Containers\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 293-307)**\n\nAfter container completion:\n1. Output files are extracted from container: `/workspace/.cloche/output/.*` → `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n2. Container stdout/stderr is captured: `Logs()` → `.cloche/<run-id>/output/container.log`\n3. Log files are indexed into the log store\n\n### Summary of File Paths\n\n**Core System Files:**\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` — gRPC service definition\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` — CLI logs command (lines 347-432)\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` — Daemon initialization\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` — Run and StepExecution types\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` — RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore interfaces\n\n**Adapter Implementations:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` — SQLite implementation (runs, captures, logs tables)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` — gRPC server with StreamLogs handler (lines 487-726)\n\n**Log Capture:**\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` — In-container agent logging\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` — Host workflow step execution and logging\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` — Unified log writer\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` — Live log pub/sub broadcaster\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` — Status message protocol\n\n**Adapters:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` — Prompt agent with streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` — Generic script adapter with streaming\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` — Container runtime (output extraction)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` — HTTP API for logs and tasks\n\nThis architecture enables:\n1. **Real-time log streaming** via the broadcaster for active runs\n2. **Persistent log storage** in the database and filesystem\n3. **Flexible log filtering** by step and log type\n4. **Multi-source output** from agent, script, and status messages\n5. **Seamless switching** between live streaming and historical log replay"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9b8e11c28901aaf4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 83012\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 49727</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"sess