[2026-03-13T20:00:03Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Gsj9T7aaFHUKZ4C6Vac5kS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012Q6qofDY55PawDf9W6GQin","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":538,"cache_read_input_tokens":14806,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":538,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SisYs2mGvpsHnZNXYBn119","session_id":"80e1ce2e-a764-409e-b43f-733763e5218d","uuid":"078d4d25-ddf7-49af-972d-97b8a8fedcf2"}
[2026-03-13T20:00:03Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012Q6qofDY55PawDf9W6GQin","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package main\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"fmt\"\n     5→\t\"os\"\n     6→)\n     7→\n     8→// subcommandHelp maps each subcommand to its detailed help text.\n     9→// Help text is formatted for LLM consumption: structured, explicit, with examples.\n    10→var subcommandHelp = map[string]string{\n    11→\t\"init\": `cloche init — Initialize a Cloche project\n    12→\n    13→Creates the .cloche/ directory with a workflow definition, Dockerfile,\n    14→prompt templates, and configuration files.\n    15→\n    16→Usage:\n    17→  cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]\n    18→\n    19→Flags:\n    20→  --workflow <name>       Name for the workflow file (default: \"develop\")\n    21→  --base-image <image>    Base Docker image for the Dockerfile (default: \"cloche-base:latest\")\n    22→\n    23→What it creates:\n    24→  .cloche/<name>.cloche           Workflow definition\n    25→  .cloche/host.cloche             Host orchestration workflow\n    26→  .cloche/Dockerfile              Container image definition\n    27→  .cloche/config.toml             Project configuration\n    28→  .cloche/prompts/implement.md    Prompt for the implement step\n    29→  .cloche/prompts/fix.md          Prompt for the fix step\n    30→  .cloche/prompts/update-docs.md  Prompt for the update-docs step\n    31→  .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh  Prompt generation script\n    32→  .cloche/version                 Schema version marker\n    33→\n    34→Existing files are never overwritten. Run this command again safely to add\n    35→missing files without losing customizations.\n    36→\n    37→Examples:\n    38→  cloche init\n    39→  cloche init --workflow build --base-image python:3.12\n    40→`,\n    41→\n    42→\t\"health\": `cloche health — Show project health summary\n    43→\n    44→Queries the daemon's HTTP API for a summary of all registered projects\n    45→and their pass/fail test counts.\n    46→\n    47→Usage:\n    48→  cloche health\n    49→\n    50→Environment:\n    51→  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (e.g. \"localhost:8080\"). Required.\n    52→\n    53→Examples:\n    54→  export CLOCHE_HTTP=localhost:8080\n    55→  cloche health\n    56→`,\n    57→\n    58→\t\"run\": `cloche run — Launch a workflow run\n    59→\n    60→Starts a new container workflow run. The daemon builds/pulls the container\n    61→image, copies the project into it, and executes the workflow steps.\n    62→\n    63→Usage:\n    64→  cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n    65→  cloche run <name>              (shorthand: bare positional workflow name)\n    66→\n    67→Flags:\n    68→  --workflow <name>    Name of the workflow to run (required). Must match a\n    69→                       .cloche/<name>.cloche file in the project.\n    70→  --prompt \"...\"       Prompt text passed to agent steps. Also available as\n    71→  -p \"...\"             the short form.\n    72→  --title \"...\"        Human-readable title for the run (shown in status/list).\n    73→  --keep-container     Do not remove the container after the run completes.\n    74→                       Useful for debugging.\n    75→\n    76→The command prints the run ID on success. Use that ID with status, logs,\n    77→poll, and stop.\n    78→\n    79→Examples:\n    80→  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add a /health endpoint\"\n    81→  cloche run develop -p \"Fix the broken CSV parser\" --title \"CSV fix\"\n    82→  cloche run --workflow build --keep-container\n    83→`,\n    84→\n    85→\t\"status\": `cloche status — Check run status\n    86→\n    87→Shows the current state of a workflow run including its type, active step,\n    88→and the result of each completed step.\n    89→\n    90→Usage:\n    91→  cloche status <run-id>\n    92→\n    93→Arguments:\n    94→  <run-id>    The run identifier returned by \"cloche run\".\n    95→\n    96→Output fields:\n    97→  Run         Run identifier\n    98→  Title       Human-readable title (if set)\n    99→  Workflow    Workflow name\n   100→  Type        \"host\" or \"container\"\n   101→  State       Current state (e.g. running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n   102→  Container   Truncated container ID (container runs only)\n   103→  Error       Error message (if failed)\n   104→  Active      Name of the currently executing step\n   105→  Steps       List of completed steps with results and timestamps\n   106→\n   107→Examples:\n   108→  cloche status abc123\n   109→`,\n   110→\n   111→\t\"logs\": `cloche logs — Show logs for a run\n   112→\n   113→Streams or displays log output for a workflow run. Supports filtering by\n   114→step name and log type, limiting output, and following live output.\n   115→\n   116→Usage:\n   117→  cloche logs <run-id> [-s <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]\n   118→\n   119→Arguments:\n   120→  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   121→\n   122→Flags:\n   123→  --step, -s <name>              Show logs only for the named step.\n   124→  --type <full|script|llm>       Filter by log type:\n   125→                                   full    — complete unfiltered output\n   126→                                   script  — script/command output only\n   127→                                   llm     — LLM interaction logs only\n   128→  --follow, -f                   Stream logs in real time (blocks until the\n   129→                                 run completes or is stopped).\n   130→  --limit, -l <n>                Display only the last n lines of output.\n   131→\n   132→Flags are combinable: cloche logs run-id -s implement -l 20 -f\n   133→\n   134→Examples:\n   135→  cloche logs abc123\n   136→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement\n   137→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20\n   138→  cloche logs abc123 -f\n   139→  cloche logs abc123 -s test --type script\n   140→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20 -f\n   141→`,\n   142→\n   143→\t\"poll\": `cloche poll — Wait for runs to finish\n   144→\n   145→Polls the daemon every 2 seconds until all runs reach a terminal state\n   146→(succeeded, failed, or cancelled).\n   147→\n   148→With a single run ID, prints step-level progress (same as before).\n   149→With multiple run IDs, displays a compact status summary.\n   150→\n   151→Usage:\n   152→  cloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n   153→\n   154→Arguments:\n   155→  <run-id>    One or more run identifiers.\n   156→\n   157→Exit codes:\n   158→  0    All runs succeeded.\n   159→  1    Any run failed, was cancelled, or the container died.\n   160→\n   161→Examples:\n   162→  cloche poll abc123\n   163→  cloche poll abc123 def456 ghi789\n   164→  cloche run develop -p \"Fix bug\" && cloche poll \"$(cloche run develop -p 'Fix bug')\"\n   165→`,\n   166→\n   167→\t\"list\": `cloche list — List workflow runs\n   168→\n   169→Shows all runs for the current project, or all runs across all projects\n   170→with --all. Results can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited\n   171→to a fixed number.\n   172→\n   173→Usage:\n   174→  cloche list [flags]\n   175→\n   176→Flags:\n   177→  --all              Show runs from all projects (default: current project only).\n   178→  --project, -p DIR  Filter by project directory.\n   179→  --state, -s STATE  Filter by run state (pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled).\n   180→  --limit, -n NUM    Limit the number of results returned.\n   181→  --issue, -i ID     Filter by issue/task ID.\n   182→\n   183→Output columns: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container),\n   184→title, container ID, and error message (if any).\n   185→\n   186→Examples:\n   187→  cloche list\n   188→  cloche list --all\n   189→  cloche list --state running\n   190→  cloche list --limit 10\n   191→  cloche list --all --state failed --limit 5\n   192→  cloche list --issue TASK-123\n   193→  cloche list -p /home/user/project -s succeeded -n 20\n   194→`,\n   195→\n   196→\t\"stop\": `cloche stop — Stop a running workflow\n   197→\n   198→Sends a stop signal to a running workflow. The container is terminated\n   199→and the run state transitions to \"cancelled\".\n   200→\n   201→Usage:\n   202→  cloche stop <run-id>\n   203→\n   204→Arguments:\n   205→  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   206→\n   207→Examples:\n   208→  cloche stop abc123\n   209→`,\n   210→\n   211→\t\"delete\": `cloche delete — Delete a retained container\n   212→\n   213→Removes a container that was kept after a run (via --keep-container).\n   214→Accepts either a container ID or a run ID.\n   215→\n   216→Usage:\n   217→  cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   218→\n   219→Arguments:\n   220→  <container-or-run-id>    Container ID or run ID to delete.\n   221→\n   222→Examples:\n   223→  cloche delete abc123\n   224→`,\n   225→\n   226→\t\"tasks\": `cloche tasks — Show task pipeline and assignment state\n   227→\n   228→Queries the daemon's HTTP API for the current task list, showing which\n   229→tasks are open, assigned, or completed.\n   230→\n   231→Usage:\n   232→  cloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   233→\n   234→Flags:\n   235→  --project <dir>    Project directory name to query (default: current\n   236→                     directory basename).\n   237→\n   238→Environment:\n   239→  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (default: \"localhost:8080\").\n   240→\n   241→Output columns: ID, STATUS, ASSIGNED, RUN, TITLE\n   242→\n   243→Examples:\n   244→  cloche tasks\n   245→  cloche tasks --project my-app\n   246→`,\n   247→\n   248→\t\"loop\": `cloche loop — Manage the orchestration loop\n   249→\n   250→Starts or stops the daemon's orchestration loop, which automatically\n   251→picks up and runs tasks from the task pipeline.\n   252→\n   253→Usage:\n   254→  cloche loop [--max <n>]     Start the orchestration loop\n   255→  cloche loop stop            Stop the orchestration loop\n   256→\n   257→Flags:\n   258→  --max <n>    Maximum number of concurrent runs (default: value from\n   259→               .cloche/config.toml).\n   260→\n   261→Examples:\n   262→  cloche loop\n   263→  cloche loop --max 3\n   264→  cloche loop stop\n   265→`,\n   266→\n   267→\t\"get\": `cloche get — Get a value from the run context store\n   268→\n   269→Reads a key from the run's context.json file. Intended for use inside\n   270→workflow scripts and steps.\n   271→\n   272→Usage:\n   273→  cloche get <key>\n   274→\n   275→Arguments:\n   276→  <key>    The context key to read.\n   277→\n   278→Environment:\n   279→  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n   280→  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n   281→\n   282→Exit codes:\n   283→  0    Key exists; value printed to stdout.\n   284→  1    Key not found or error.\n   285→\n   286→Examples:\n   287→  cloche get branch\n   288→  cloche get task_id\n   289→`,\n   290→\n   291→\t\"set\": `cloche set — Set a value in the run context store\n   292→\n   293→Writes a key-value pair to the run's context.json file. Use \"-\" as the\n   294→value to read from stdin (useful for multi-line content).\n   295→\n   296→Usage:\n   297→  cloche set <key> <value>\n   298→  cloche set <key> -          (read value from stdin)\n   299→\n   300→Arguments:\n   301→  <key>      The context key to write.\n   302→  <value>    The value to store, or \"-\" to read from stdin.\n   303→\n   304→Environment:\n   305→  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n   306→  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n   307→\n   308→Examples:\n   309→  cloche set branch feature-auth\n   310→  echo \"multi-line content\" | cloche set notes -\n   311→`,\n   312→\n   313→\t\"workflow\": `cloche workflow — View workflow definitions\n   314→\n   315→Lists all workflows in the project or renders a specific workflow as an\n   316→ASCII-art graph showing steps, wiring, and result paths.\n   317→\n   318→Usage:\n   319→  cloche workflow [--project <dir>]          List all workflows\n   320→  cloche workflow <name> [--project <dir>]   Show workflow graph\n   321→\n   322→Arguments:\n   323→  <name>    Name of the workflow to render as a graph.\n   324→\n   325→Flags:\n   326→  --project <dir>, -p <dir>    Project directory (default: current directory).\n   327→\n   328→When listing, workflows are grouped by type (container or host). When\n   329→showing a specific workflow, the output is a graph with step boxes and\n   330→colored wires: green for success, red for fail/failed, and\n   331→blue/yellow/orange/magenta for other result paths. Wires to the same\n   332→destination are merged for readability.\n   333→\n   334→Examples:\n   335→  cloche workflow\n   336→  cloche workflow develop\n   337→  cloche workflow main -p /path/to/project\n   338→  cloche workflow --project ../other-project\n   339→`,\n   340→\n   341→\t\"project\": `cloche project — Show project info and config\n   342→\n   343→Displays project-level information including config settings, orchestrator\n   344→loop state, concurrency, active runs, and known workflows.\n   345→\n   346→By default, looks up the project by the current working directory. Use\n   347→--name to look up a project by its label instead.\n   348→\n   349→Usage:\n   350→  cloche project [--name <label>]\n   351→\n   352→Flags:\n   353→  --name <label>    Look up project by label (e.g. \"cloche\") instead of\n   354→                    the current directory.\n   355→\n   356→Output includes:\n   357→  Config            active, concurrency, stagger, dedup, evolution settings\n   358→  Loop              Orchestration loop state (running or stopped)\n   359→  Active runs       Currently pending or running workflow runs\n   360→  Workflows         Known container and host workflow names\n   361→\n   362→Environment:\n   363→  CLOCHE_ADDR    Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n   364→\n   365→Examples:\n   366→  cloche project\n   367→  cloche project --name cloche\n   368→  cloche project --name my-app\n   369→`,\n   370→\n   371→\t\"shutdown\": `cloche shutdown — Shut down the daemon\n   372→\n   373→Sends a shutdown signal to the Cloche daemon. All running workflows are\n   374→stopped and the daemon process exits.\n   375→\n   376→Usage:\n   377→  cloche shutdown\n   378→\n   379→Examples:\n   380→  cloche shutdown\n   381→`,\n   382→}\n   383→\n   384→// printHelp prints the top-level help or subcommand-specific help.\n   385→// Returns true if help was printed (caller should exit).\n   386→func printHelp(args []string) bool {\n   387→\tif len(args) == 0 {\n   388→\t\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n   389→\t\treturn true\n   390→\t}\n   391→\n   392→\t// \"cloche help <subcommand>\"\n   393→\tcmd := args[0]\n   394→\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n   395→\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n   396→\t\treturn true\n   397→\t}\n   398→\n   399→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"unknown command: %s\\n\\n\", cmd)\n   400→\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n   401→\treturn true\n   402→}\n   403→\n   404→// hasHelpFlag returns true if the args contain --help or -h.\n   405→func hasHelpFlag(args []string) bool {\n   406→\tfor _, arg := range args {\n   407→\t\tif arg == \"--help\" || arg == \"-h\" {\n   408→\t\t\treturn true\n   409→\t\t}\n   410→\t}\n   411→\treturn false\n   412→}\n   413→\n   414→// printSubcommandHelp prints help for a subcommand and exits.\n   415→func printSubcommandHelp(cmd string) {\n   416→\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n   417→\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n   418→\t} else {\n   419→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"no help available for %q\\n\", cmd)\n   420→\t}\n   421→}\n   422→\n   423→func printTopLevelHelp() {\n   424→\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, `cloche — Grow-code high quality applications\n   425→\n   426→Cloche provides containerized environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL\n   427→for linking agentic and script-driven tasks, and validated code pipelines.\n   428→\n   429→Usage:\n   430→  cloche <command> [args]\n   431→  cloche help <command>       Show detailed help for a command\n   432→  cloche <command> --help     Same as above\n   433→\n   434→Project Setup:\n   435→  init       Initialize a Cloche project (.cloche/ directory and templates)\n   436→  health     Show project health summary (pass/fail counts)\n   437→  project    Show project info, config, loop state, and workflows\n   438→\n   439→Workflow Info:\n   440→  workflow   List workflows or show a workflow as an ASCII-art graph\n   441→\n   442→Workflow Runs:\n   443→  run        Launch a workflow run in a container\n   444→  status     Check run status (state, steps, errors)\n   445→  logs       Show or stream logs for a run\n   446→  poll       Wait for one or more runs to finish (blocks until terminal)\n   447→  list       List runs for current project (or all projects)\n   448→  stop       Stop a running workflow\n   449→  delete     Delete a retained container\n   450→\n   451→Orchestration:\n   452→  tasks      Show task pipeline and assignment state\n   453→  loop       Start or stop the orchestration loop\n   454→\n   455→Context Store (for use inside workflow steps):\n   456→  get        Get a value from the run context store\n   457→  set        Set a value in the run context store\n   458→\n   459→Daemon:\n   460→  shutdown   Shut down the Cloche daemon\n   461→\n   462→Environment Variables:\n   463→  CLOCHE_ADDR          Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n   464→  CLOCHE_HTTP          Daemon HTTP address (for health/tasks commands)\n   465→  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run ID for get/set commands (set automatically in steps)\n   466→  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory override for get/set commands\n   467→\n   468→Examples:\n   469→  cloche init\n   470→  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add user authentication\"\n   471→  cloche status abc123\n   472→  cloche logs abc123 --follow\n   473→  cloche list\n   474→  cloche loop --max 2\n   475→`)\n   476→}\n   477→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SisYs2mGvpsHnZNXYBn119","session_id":"80e1ce2e-a764-409e-b43f-733763e5218d","uuid":"7bcc0c89-7510-48f4-8e44-3526d06e58cd"}
