[2026-03-13T20:00:03Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_019QdwaMHWBTvZ4fQq6ghygo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XQUit1DuCSWF43FmkwHvzT","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16729,"cache_read_input_tokens":15370,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":16729,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01X39tUhxFjzAhiJaof3xvLs","session_id":"80e1ce2e-a764-409e-b43f-733763e5218d","uuid":"fed53d26-d993-4de3-91c1-2dafe3922ed1"}
[2026-03-13T20:00:03Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XQUit1DuCSWF43FmkwHvzT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Installation\n     2→\n     3→This document covers the various ways to install Cloche on your machine.\n     4→\n     5→## Prerequisites\n     6→\n     7→All installation methods require:\n     8→\n     9→- **Docker** — Cloche runs workflows in containers\n    10→- **Git** — result extraction uses git worktrees\n    11→\n    12→## Build from Source\n    13→\n    14→Clone the repository, build the binaries and Docker image, and install them:\n    15→\n    16→```\n    17→git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    18→cd cloche\n    19→make install\n    20→```\n    21→\n    22→`make install` builds all three binaries (`cloche`, `cloched`, `cloche-agent`),\n    23→builds the `cloche-agent:latest` Docker image, installs the binaries to\n    24→`~/.local/bin/`, and starts the daemon. You can change the install prefix:\n    25→\n    26→```\n    27→make install PREFIX=/usr/local\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→Make sure the install prefix is on your `PATH`:\n    31→\n    32→```\n    33→export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n    34→```\n    35→\n    36→### Build Requirements\n    37→\n    38→- Go 1.25+\n    39→\n    40→## `go install`\n    41→\n    42→If you have Go installed, you can install the binaries directly:\n    43→\n    44→```\n    45→go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche@latest\n    46→go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloched@latest\n    47→go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche-agent@latest\n    48→```\n    49→\n    50→This places the binaries in `$GOPATH/bin` (or `$HOME/go/bin` by default).\n    51→\n    52→You still need to build the Docker image separately. Clone the repository and\n    53→run:\n    54→\n    55→```\n    56→git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    57→cd cloche\n    58→make docker-build\n    59→```\n    60→\n    61→## Pre-built Release Binaries (Planned)\n    62→\n    63→> **Note:** Pre-built release binaries are not yet available. This section\n    64→> describes the planned installation method for when releases are published.\n    65→\n    66→Download pre-built binaries from the\n    67→[GitHub Releases](https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases) page. Each\n    68→release will include archives for common platforms (Linux amd64, Linux arm64,\n    69→macOS amd64, macOS arm64).\n    70→\n    71→```\n    72→# Example: Linux amd64\n    73→curl -LO https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases/latest/download/cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\n    74→tar xzf cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\n    75→sudo install cloche cloched cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/\n    76→```\n    77→\n    78→You still need to build the Docker image. Clone the repo and run\n    79→`make docker-build`:\n    80→\n    81→```\n    82→git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    83→cd cloche\n    84→make docker-build\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→## Homebrew (macOS / Linux) (Planned)\n    88→\n    89→> **Note:** A Homebrew tap is not yet published. This section describes the\n    90→> planned installation method.\n    91→\n    92→```\n    93→brew tap cloche-dev/tap\n    94→brew install cloche\n    95→```\n    96→\n    97→This will install all three binaries. You will still need the Docker image —\n    98→the formula will print post-install instructions for building or pulling it.\n    99→\n   100→## Verifying the Installation\n   101→\n   102→After installing, verify that everything works:\n   103→\n   104→```\n   105→# Check versions\n   106→cloche --version\n   107→\n   108→# Start the daemon (if not already running)\n   109→cloched &\n   110→\n   111→# Build the agent image\n   112→make docker-build\n   113→\n   114→# Run a quick test from any git repository with a .cloche/ directory\n   115→cloche list\n   116→```\n   117→\n   118→## Upgrading\n   119→\n   120→To upgrade an existing installation, repeat your original installation method.\n   121→If you built from source:\n   122→\n   123→```\n   124→cd cloche\n   125→git pull\n   126→make install\n   127→```\n   128→\n   129→The `make install` target stops the running daemon, installs the new binaries,\n   130→and restarts the daemon automatically.\n   131→\n   132→## Next Steps\n   133→\n   134→- [Usage guide](USAGE.md) — quick start, CLI reference, and workflow setup\n   135→- [Workflow DSL reference](workflows.md) — full syntax for `.cloche` files\n   136→- [How to set up Claude Code](agent-setup-claude.md) — container setup for Claude\n   137→- [How to set up Codex](agent-setup-codex.md) — container setup for Codex\n   138→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01X39tUhxFjzAhiJaof3xvLs","session_id":"80e1ce2e-a764-409e-b43f-733763e5218d","uuid":"2dc1903e-7bc9-4c0b-8f4a-a51a0df50087"}
